/node_modules/
.expo/
# dist/ is intentionally NOT ignored — Render's Python runtime build has no
# reliable modern Node (reports Node 14, too old for Expo SDK 54), so the web
# export is built locally and committed rather than built at deploy time.
# Rebuild with: npx expo export --platform web
#
# node_modules/ above is anchored to the repo root (leading slash) rather than
# a bare "node_modules/", which would also match dist/assets/node_modules/ —
# Expo's web export vendors @expo/vector-icons' font files under a path that
# happens to be named node_modules, and a bare pattern silently dropped them
# from every dist commit (confirmed: 0 files tracked under
# dist/assets/node_modules/ despite `git add mobile/dist`), which is why
# every icon in the deployed PWA rendered as an empty square — the font file
# itself was never in the repo, so Render served the SPA-fallback index.html
# (200, wrong content-type) for every font request instead of a 404.
npm-debug.*
*.jks
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision
*.orig.*
web-build/
.env
android/
ios/

